<problem>
  <p>Calculate the following for even \(n\)</p>
  <ul><li>\(\binom{n}{0}+\binom{n}{1}+\ldots+\binom{n}{n}\)</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
    <choice correct="false">\(\binom{2n}{n}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n}{n/2}\)</choice>
    <choice correct="true">\(2^n\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(2^{n-1}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
  <ul><li>\(\binom{n}{0}-\binom{n}{1}+\binom{n}{2}-\ldots+\binom{n}{n}\)</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n}{n/2}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(2^{n-1}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(n/2\)</choice>
  <choice correct="true">\(0\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
  <ul><li>\(\binom{n}{0}^2+\binom{n}{1}^2+\ldots+\binom{n}{n}^2\) (hint: \(\binom{n}{i}^2=\binom{n}{i}\binom{n}{10-i}\))</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
  <choice correct="true">\(\binom{2n}{n}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n}{n/2}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(2^n\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(2^{n-1}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
<p>Calculate the following for odd \(n\)</p>
  <ul><li>\(\binom{n}{1}+\binom{n}{3}+\binom{n}{5}+\ldots+\binom{n}{n}\)</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{2n}{n}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n}{n/2}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(2^{n}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="true">\(2^{n-1}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
<p>Calculate the following for \(r\le n\)</p>
  <ul><li>\(\binom{r}{r}+\binom{r+1}{r}+\ldots+\binom{n}{r}\)</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{2n}{r}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n}{r+1}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n+1}{n-r}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="true">\(\binom{n+1}{r+1}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
  <ul><li>\(\binom{n-r}{0}+\binom{n-r+1}{1}+\ldots+\binom{n}{r}\)</li></ul>
<multiplechoiceresponse>
<choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{2n}{n-r}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n+1}{r+1}\)</choice>  
  <choice correct="false">\(\binom{n+1}{n-r}\)</choice>
  <choice correct="true">\(\binom{n+1}{n-r+1}\)</choice>
  </choicegroup>
</multiplechoiceresponse>
  
<solution>
<div class="detailed-solution">
<p>Explanation</p>

<p>Hockey-Stick Identity: \(\sum_{i=r}^n\binom{n}{r}=\binom{n+1}{r+1}\) for \(n>r\)</p>

</div>
</solution>
</problem>
